com.darwinreforged.server.core.commands.annotations

Annotation Type Command


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={METHOD,TYPE})
public @interface Command
    The interface Command.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      java.lang.String[] aliases
      A list of aliases for the command.
      java.lang.String desc
      Desc string.
      java.lang.String usage
      Usage instruction.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      boolean anyFlags
      Get whether any flag can be used.
      java.lang.String[] args
      A list of argument names in order of their position inside the command syntax.
      java.lang.String[] flags
      Flags allow special processing for flags such as -h in the command, allowing users to easily turn on a flag.
      java.lang.String help
      Help string.
      boolean injectLocations
      Whether or not location type should be injected into the parameters, if false the command cannot register if it has location parameter types.
      boolean join
      Get whether remaining arguments are joined into a single String object.
      int max
      The maximum number of arguments.
      int min
      The minimum number of arguments.
      boolean parseArgs
      Get whether argument values should be parsed into native types.
      boolean parseFlags
      Get whether flag values should be parsed into native types.
      java.lang.String[] valueFlags
      Flags allow special processing for flags such as -t [type] in the command, allowing users to easily turn on a flag.

    • Element Detail

      • aliases

        public abstract java.lang.String[] aliases
        A list of aliases for the command. The first alias is the most important -- it is the main name of the command. (The method name is never used for anything).
        Returns:
        Aliases for a command

      • usage

        public abstract java.lang.String usage
        Usage instruction. Example text for usage could be [-h harps] [name] [message].
        Returns:
        Usage instructions for a command

      • desc

        public abstract java.lang.String desc
        Desc string.
        Returns:
        A short description for the command.

      • min

        public abstract int min
        The minimum number of arguments. This should be 0 or above.
        Returns:
        the minimum number of arguments
        Default:
        0

      • max

        public abstract int max
        The maximum number of arguments. Use -1 for an unlimited number of arguments.
        Returns:
        the maximum number of arguments
        Default:
        -1

      • flags

        public abstract java.lang.String[] flags
        Flags allow special processing for flags such as -h in the command, allowing users to easily turn on a flag. Use A-Z+ and a-z+ as possible flags.
        Returns:
        Flags matching a-zA-Z+
        Default:
        ""

      • valueFlags

        public abstract java.lang.String[] valueFlags
        Flags allow special processing for flags such as -t [type] in the command, allowing users to easily turn on a flag. Use A-Z+ and a-z+ as possible flags. These flags will be parsed with their value being the first argument behind it.
        Returns:
        Flags matching a-zA-Z+
        Default:
        ""

      • help

        public abstract java.lang.String help
        Help string.
        Returns:
        A long description for the command.
        Default:
        ""

      • anyFlags

        public abstract boolean anyFlags
        Get whether any flag can be used. Only affects flags().
        Returns:
        true if so
        Default:
        false

      • join

        public abstract boolean join
        Get whether remaining arguments are joined into a single String object. Requires max() to be greater than 0.
        Returns:
        true if so
        Default:
        false

      • parseFlags

        public abstract boolean parseFlags
        Get whether flag values should be parsed into native types. Requires flags() or anyFlags() to be present.
        Returns:
        true if so
        Default:
        false

      • parseArgs

        public abstract boolean parseArgs
        Get whether argument values should be parsed into native types.
        Returns:
        true if so
        Default:
        false

      • injectLocations

        public abstract boolean injectLocations
        Whether or not location type should be injected into the parameters, if false the command cannot register if it has location parameter types.
        Returns:
        true if so
        Default:
        true

      • args

        public abstract java.lang.String[] args
        A list of argument names in order of their position inside the command syntax. Requires max() to be present
        Returns:
        Argument names
        Default:
        ""
